# Timucua language  

The '''Timucua language''' (pronounced [&#91;tiˈmuːkwa&#93;](/Help:IPA)) was an extinct language isolate spoken by the [Timucua](/Timucua) peoples in what is now the [U.S. states of Florida and Georgia](/Florida) and parts of [Eastern Texas](/Texas).  Its speakers were organized into a network of tribal groups that shared a common linguistic ancestry but maintained distinct local identities.  The language vanished in the late 18th century after a series of epidemics, wars, and forced migrations that decimated the Timucua population; by the time Spanish authorities recorded its final remnants, only a handful of elderly speakers remained.  

